==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: door-to-door
<hw>door-to-door</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>direct without
intermediate changes of vehicle; -- of e.g. journeys or deliveries;
<as>as, the limousine offers direct <ex>door-to-door</ex>
service</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>omitting no one; from the door of one house to that
of the next; <as>as, a <ex>door-to-door</ex> solicitation, canvass, or
campaign</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> house-to-house.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doorway</ent>⟦br⟧
